SIMPLE: frosty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frosty
<hw>Frost"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>fyrstig</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Attended with, or producing,
frost; having power to congeal water; cold; freezing; <as>as, a
<ex>frosty</ex> night</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Covered with frost; <as>as, the grass is
<ex>frosty</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Chill in affection; without warmth of affection or
courage.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Appearing as if covered with hoarfrost; white;
gray-haired; <as>as, a <ex>frosty</ex> head</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frote</ent>⟦br⟧
